item.description:
@roguex wrote:

[quote=“Budda, post:2, topic:228374”]Go into My Computer>C Drive>Windows and delete the system32 folder in there. I had this same problem a while back, and its just because the system32 folder has things in it that windows thinks is important, but aren’t and they normally just screw everything up.
Hope I helped![/quote]

Your so funny.

First you need JDK installed if compiling http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp if you already have that installed check the location of where it is installed the latest jdk should be like this C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_07, if that is correct go into your .bat or compiler and check that it is pointing to the right directory for the java.

IF EXIST “%programfiles%\JAVA\JDK1.6.0_07\BIN” (GOTO COM05)

Hope that helps.
